description: {"blocks":[{"key":"e2vh3","text":"This protocol is intended as a guideline to perform the Reverse Transcription procedure to detect and quantify miRNAs. This method use TaqMan® MicroRNA Assays and Applied Biosystems real-time PCR instruments. The assays can detect and quantify small RNA in 1 to 10 ng of total RNA with a dynamic range of greater than six logs. This protocol works on detecting microRNA from samples that were purified from plasma and serum. All samples were stored at -80ºC until the realization of the RT procedure. The aim of this protocol is to use a miRNA-specifc, stem-loop RT primer, in order to produce cDNA from miRNA samples. The amplified products of RT procedure will then be used to perform qPCR or rtPCR.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"h0ok","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7e16o","text":"Place the RT mix on ice until you prepare the RNA reaction.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"57cs7","text":"Allow the reagents and samples to thaw on ice.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"88adh","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7rr53","text":"Before use, mix gently and centrifuge briefly.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"g3il","text":"Thaw the 5✕ RT primer from the TaqMan® MicroRNA Assays (target and control) on ice.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"24sjg","text":"Thaw the diluted samples (2 ng/μL) on ice.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"939a6","text":"Before use, vortex the RT primer tubes to mix, then centrifuge briefly.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8gn67","text":"Prepare a 0.2 ml tube for each sample.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8mku5","text":"Label the lid of the tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7304i","text":"For each 15-μL RT reaction, combine RT mix (from step 2) with miRNA sample and 5X RT primer in the ratio of:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"vfrt","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e75ql","text":"- 7 μL of RT master mix","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5aff5","text":"- 5 μL of miRNA sample (2 ng/μL per reaction)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7ph5f","text":"- 3 μL of 5X RT primer from each assay into the corresponding RT reaction tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"aed0s","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"eemr4","text":"Note: Before opening the RT primer tubes, thaw the tubes on ice and mix by vortexing, then centrifuge them.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"co3mn","text":"Seal the tubes and mix gently.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9tjgf","text":"Centrifuge briefly to bring the solution to the bottom of the tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5ds6j","text":"Incubate the tube on ice for 5 minutes and keep it on ice until you are ready to load the thermal cycler.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
